With the news that someone has found a sponge that looks like cookie monster and prodded by certain people, I really just couldn&rsquo;t resist the following&hellip;
What, it&rsquo;s Wednesday!
Original images &copy; Mauricio Handler

When it&rsquo;s wavy out&hellip;
Coffee, laptop, scope, and a red alga that looks pretty much like every other red alga in the tank&hellip;time for some IDs.
SCIENCE!

Several years ago, when the Yeti crab, Kiwa hirsuta was first described, the world looked at a crustacean for the first time and went, &ldquo;AWWWWW!!!&rdquo;
I mean, how could you know love crabs from the Kiwa genus? They have fuzzy arms! And are adorable! People immediately began paying tribute with plush toys of all manner and even decorative food arrangements.
So what could be better than a plain ole&rsquo; Yeti crab?

So, what am I up to? Where&rsquo;s my research program going? What occupied my mind these days? I think cephalopodcast may have answered some of this with a recent post in which they linked the following movie.
It provides a frightening insight into my current state of mind&hellip;
